Copyright (C) 1994, 1995, 1996, 1999, 2000, 2001, 2002, 2004, 2005,
2006 Free Software Foundation, Inc.

This file is free documentation; the Free Software Foundation gives
unlimited permission to copy, distribute and modify it.

To configure
==================

./configure --with-pnetcdf=/path/to/pnetcdf \
            MPICC=mpi_c_compiler

make

Note that the MPI C compiler must be compatible with the one used to
build PnetCDF library.


To Install
==================

make install

The default installion location is ./run under the build directory.
The executable, named gcrm_io, will be copied over to the installion
directory, along with several parameter files.

Command-line input parameter files:
    zgrd.in      - the default (if no parameter file is given on command line)
    zgrd.in.r6   - level_max = 6
    zgrd.in.r7   - level_max = 7
    zgrd.in.r8   - level_max = 8
    zgrd.in.r9   - level_max = 9
    zgrd.in.r10  - level_max = 10
    zgrd.in.r11  - level_max = 11

GCRM simulation specific parameter file
    ZGrd.desc               - description of all grid and field variables
                              contains information about the size, type
                              and dimension of each variable.

Parameter files for I/O configuration. Only one of the following files should
be used by the option of "io_config_file" in zgrd.in.
    ZGrd.CP.fcfg            -
    ZGrd.CP.lyr.fcfg        -
    ZGrd.CP.lyr.fcfg.groups -
    ZGrd.CP.lyr.fcfg.one    -
    ZGrd.LZ.fcfg.nophys     -


`configure' Invocation
======================

`configure' recognizes the following options to control how it operates.

`--help'
`-h'
     Print a summary of the options to `configure', and exit.

`--version'
`-V'
     Print the version of Autoconf used to generate the `configure'
     script, and exit.

`--cache-file=FILE'
     Enable the cache: use and save the results of the tests in FILE,
     traditionally `config.cache'.  FILE defaults to `/dev/null' to
     disable caching.

`--config-cache'
`-C'
     Alias for `--cache-file=config.cache'.

`--quiet'
`--silent'
`-q'
     Do not print messages saying which checks are being made.  To
     suppress all normal output, redirect it to `/dev/null' (any error
     messages will still be shown).

`--srcdir=DIR'
     Look for the package's source code in directory DIR.  Usually
     `configure' can determine that directory automatically.

`configure' also accepts some other, not widely useful, options.  Run
`configure --help' for more details.

